{"image_id": "ZBRA_2005_page_43", "image_size": [1650, 1275], "ocr": [{"text": "F-10", "bbox": [75.0, 1223.3, 93.3, 1238.5]}, {"text": "eligible for an automatic grant at the time at which an automatic grant would otherwise", "bbox": [75.0, 146.7, 776.8, 166.7]}, {"text": "be made, then each eligible non-employee director shall receive an option to purchase a", "bbox": [75.0, 167.5, 784.9, 187.5]}, {"text": "pro rata number of shares. As of December 31, 2005, 187,932 shares were available under", "bbox": [75.0, 188.4, 793.7, 208.3]}, {"text": "the plan. Unless otherwise provided in an option agreement, options granted under the", "bbox": [75.0, 209.2, 778.2, 229.2]}, {"text": "2002 Director Plan shall become exercisable in five equal increments beginning on the", "bbox": [75.0, 230.0, 768.9, 250.0]}, {"text": "date of the grant and on each of the first four anniversaries thereof. All options expire", "bbox": [75.0, 250.9, 761.8, 270.8]}, {"text": "on the earlier of (a) ten years following the grant date, (b) the first anniversary of the", "bbox": [75.0, 271.7, 752.4, 291.7]}, {"text": "termination date of the non-employee director’s directorship for any reason other than", "bbox": [75.0, 292.5, 772.2, 312.5]}, {"text": "those listed in clause (c) below, or (c) the termination of the non-employee director’s", "bbox": [75.0, 313.4, 755.6, 333.3]}, {"text": "directorship by Zebra’s stockholders for cause, or resignation for cause, in each case as", "bbox": [75.0, 334.2, 778.9, 354.2]}, {"text": "defined in the option agreement.", "bbox": [75.0, 355.0, 337.5, 375.0]}, {"text": "On February 7, 2006, Zebra’s Board of Directors approved the 2006 Zebra Technologies", "bbox": [75.0, 396.7, 774.2, 416.7]}, {"text": "Corporation Incentive Compensation Plan (the 2006 Plan) and will submit such plan to", "bbox": [75.0, 417.5, 767.6, 437.5]}, {"text": "the stockholders at our Annual Meeting of Stockholders scheduled for May 9, 2006. If", "bbox": [75.0, 438.4, 760.9, 458.3]}, {"text": "approved by the stockholders, the 2006 Plan will become effective immediately and", "bbox": [75.0, 459.2, 748.8, 479.2]}, {"text": "supersede the 1997 Stock Option Plan (the 1997 Plan) and the 2002 Non-Employee", "bbox": [75.0, 480.0, 736.3, 500.0]}, {"text": "Director Stock Option Plan (the 2002 Director Plan). The aggregate number of shares", "bbox": [75.0, 500.9, 755.7, 520.8]}, {"text": "that would be available under the 2006 Plan is 5,500,000 (which include 2,535,945", "bbox": [75.0, 521.7, 730.7, 541.7]}, {"text": "unissued shares from the 1997 Plan and the 2002 Director Plan). The types of awards that", "bbox": [75.0, 542.6, 792.7, 562.5]}, {"text": "would be available under the 2006 Plan are incentive stock options, nonqualified stock", "bbox": [75.0, 563.4, 768.2, 583.3]}, {"text": "options, stock appreciation rights, restricted stock, performance shares and units and", "bbox": [75.0, 584.2, 764.4, 604.2]}, {"text": "performance-based cash bonuses. Employees, directors and consultants of the Company", "bbox": [75.0, 605.1, 795.4, 625.0]}, {"text": "and its subsidiaries would be eligible to participate in the 2006 Plan.", "bbox": [75.0, 625.9, 622.5, 645.8]}, {"text": "For purposes of calculating the compensation cost consistent with SFAS No. 123, the fair", "bbox": [75.0, 667.6, 789.3, 687.5]}, {"text": "value of each stock option granted prior to January 1, 2005, is estimated on the date of", "bbox": [75.0, 688.4, 770.1, 708.3]}, {"text": "grant using the Black-Scholes option-pricing model. For stock options granted on or after", "bbox": [75.0, 709.2, 793.2, 729.2]}, {"text": "January 1, 2005, fair value is estimated on the date of grant using a binomial model. The", "bbox": [843.8, 146.7, 1552.6, 166.7]}, {"text": "following table shows the weighted-average assumptions used for stock option grants as", "bbox": [843.8, 167.5, 1562.3, 187.5]}, {"text": "well as the fair value of the options granted based on those assumptions:", "bbox": [843.8, 188.4, 